org.kocakosm.pitaya.net

Class MediaType

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.kocakosm.pitaya.net.MediaType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public final class MediaType
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Represents an Internet Media Type. This class also supports the concept of media ranges defined by HTTP/1.1. The * character is treated as a wildcard and is used to represent any acceptable type or subtype value. All values for type, subtype, parameter attributes or parameter values must be valid according to RFCs 2045 and 2046. All portions of the media type that are case-insensitive (type, subtype, parameter attributes) are normalized to lowercase. Parameters' values are not modified except for the charset parameter which is normalised to uppercase. Instances of this class are immutable.
    Since:
    0.3
    Author:
    Osman KOCAK
    See Also:
    RFC 2045, RFC 2046, RFC 2616 (ยง 14.1), Serialized Form

      • is

        public boolean is(MediaType range)
        Returns whether this media type is within the specified media range. Namely, it returns true if the type of range is the wildcard or is equal to the type of this instance, and, if the subtype of range is the wildcard or is equal to the subtype of this instance, and, if all the parameters present in range are also present in this instance.
        Parameters:
        range - the range to check this media type against.
        Returns:
        whether this media type is within the specified range.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if range is null.
